<TITLE> 18 killed in road accidents across country </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)At least 18 people were killed and more than 100 injured in road accidents across the country on Friday, as highways were crowded with holiday traffic a day ahead of Eid. In Jamalpur, three people including a police constable were killed and 40 injured in a bus accident on Jamalpur-Madarganj road at around 8pm, police said. Officer-in-charge of Madarganj Police Station told bdnews24.com the Madarganj-bound local bus fell into a roadside ditch as it lost control near Jotiapara. Police constable Shafiqul Islam, 35, 'Montu', 26, and 'Shaheen', 18, died on the spot. Eleven among the injured were taken to Madarganj General Hospital and others to different hospitals. In Madaripur, five people were killed and 40 others injured on the Dhaka-Khulna highway at around 11am. The injured were admitted to local hospitals in Faridpur, Bhanga and Shibchar. Shibchar Police Station sub-inspector Sabur Hossain said a Dhaka bound bus collided with a Khulna bound bus killing four passengers on the spot. Another succumbed to injuries in hospital, Hossain said. Two of the dead were identified as Belal Hossain, 21, and 'Shipon', 20, of Sidikhan Chardaulatpur village of Kalkini upazila. In Dinajpur, two people were killed after a bus hit their motorcycle on the Dianajpur-Thakurgaon highway at around 6am, police said. A third person, also a passenger on the bike, was admitted to Rangpur Medical College Hospital in a critical condition. The dead were identified as 18 year-old Saidur Rahman and 21 year-old 'Yousuf'. The injured man was Shahinur Islam. Police said five people were killed and 20 others injured in a bus accident on the Doulatdia-Khulna highway near Goaland bus stand in Rajbari. Goaland Police Station sub-inspector Mizanur Rahman said a Jessore bound bus lost control and crashed into a ditch at around 5:30am leaving four passengers dead on the spot. Another died on the way to hospital. Of the dead, three were immediately identified as 35-year old Abdur Razzak, 19 year-old Ismail of Satkhira and Shafiur Rahman Shafi of Jessore, Rahman said. Another three people were killed Friday morning in two separate accidents in Tangail, said police. Mirzapur police chief Habibullah Sarkar said a Rangpur bound bus crashed off the Dhaka-Tangail highway leaving two passengers dead and 15 injured. The dead were identified as 25 year-old Azimuddin of Rangpur and 35 year-old Mobashsher Alam of Gaibandha. The injured were taken to Kumudini Hospital, Sarkar said. An unidentified man died after falling from the top of a moving truck in Tangail Sadar Upazila, said locals. bdnews24.c
